sub_title: Global Business Analyst at Royal Philips
summary:
A multi-cultural background and a diverse, international education enable me to offer unique perspectives. During my adventures, I’ve learned that I derive energy from interactions with people and often find myself offering advice. During work, I seamlessly integrate into my roles, through swiftly learning on the job and proactive engagement. I aspire to work as a data-driven problem-solver in the fields of digital marketing or consulting.

Before my bachelor's degree, I did a six-month marketing internship in Jakarta which was followed by a five-month design course in Melbourne. || As a practical side note, I hold European citizenship.

[{'title': 'MAEUR Neuromarketing & Innovation Event', 'date': {'start': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}, 'end': {'month': 8, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}}, 'description': 'Day Organization Coordinator

What is neuromarketing and how does it affect us? We’ve all heard that companies have been using it to capitalize on our brain’s shortcomings, but how? As it has become increasingly relevant in the marketing field, we want to provide you with insights into the theories behind and the applications in neuromarketing. We offered an interactive and introductory talk to provide a theoretical background, followed by hands-on workshops with companies that engage in neuromarketing practices (Alpha.One & NN Investments). The man who coined the term ‘neuromarketing’, Prof. Ale Smidts, introduced this field. The event took place on April 13th and 14th, 2021.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Sanam', 'last_name': 'Vaswani', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Global Business Analyst at Royal Philips'}]}, {'title': 'We Are Cohort 8: Leaders of Tomorrow Yearbook', 'date': {'start': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}, 'end': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}}, 'description': 'Lead Yearbook Designer

Het Bèkske originated as a project from the Mukomeze Foundation, which focuses on supporting female survivors of sexual violence from the genocide in Rwanda through the sale of the coffee beans that the women grow. Along with a team of six others, we organized two events in Tilburg to raise awareness about the 100 day commemoration of the  25th anniversary of the Genocide against the Tutsis in Rwanda. Alongside this, we engaged in social media and marketing campaigns. I lead and produced the graphic design and video content.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Sanam', 'last_name': 'Vaswani', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Global Business Analyst at Royal Philips'}]}, {'title': 'Closer to Home', 'date': {'start': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}, 'end': {'month': 7, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}}, 'description': 'Lend a Hand is a non-profit organisation aiming to empower children from less fortunate backgrounds. This event was a collaboration between Outreaching Honors Program and Tilburg University Blockchain Association.

Wim Maas kicked off the event with the origins of accountancy and its challenges. Next, Alexej Jordanov, the founder of BLOX, a blockchain-oriented startup incubator. He displayed introduced blockchain's potential beyond just currency applications. The subsequent speaker was Kim Raath, co-founder of topl.co, an open capital infrastructure for developing markets. She presented what her team had done with regards to building an application on a blockchain-based system. The event ended with the introduction of Bitcoin and Bitcoin cash by Alejandro de la Torre. He showcased the unique challenges that the bitcoin had faced as a currency and a technology and how people intended to fix it. The event was held on the 18th of May 2018.", 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Sanam', 'last_name': 'Vaswani', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Global Business Analyst at Royal Philips'}]}]
